snippet.textDisplay:
OMG so much stupidity and ignorance in these comments, drives me mad. So, here we go:

1. Gretel has always been the character with the most complete arc in the fairy tale by the brothers Grimm. READ THE FREAKING STORY. It's obvious. She starts by being a scared girl depending on her brother to solve the problems around her, and ends up tricking the witch to have herself and her brother.
2. The rearrangement of the names is not because of "political correctness" or feminism, it's because GRETEL is the protagonist in this interpretation of the story. If you want to watch "Hansel and Gretel" there are plenty of other movies out there that respect that aspect of the story.
3. There are TONS of analysis on the fairy tale, suggesting that the witch was making Gretel go through an initiation on witchcraft.

AND, 4: You don't know nor care a shit about fairy tales, so please think about that before you open your mouth.
